Anonymous Mon 03 Oct 2022 02:43:52 No.51365230 Report

Dinner time cometh bitches.
sweet mesquite Chili
This is a warm non-spicy Chili if you want a little spicy add 1 tsp of cayenne pepper, if you want hotter mince finely 1 serrano pepper.

What you need

1 crock pot that holds 4-6 quarts MINIMUM
1 deep pan/pot/dutch-oven (should hold at LEAST half as much as above)
1 Blender, or get to mincing and mixing.

1 15.5Oz can kidney beans
1 40Oz can pinto beans
1-2 lbs. 15% fat ground beef
1 tbsp mesquite seasoning
1 tsp black pepper
1/2 tsp white pepper
1 pack McCormick chili seasoning mild/reg
1 tsp sage
1/2 tsp garlic salt
1/2 tsp onion salt
1 tsp cumin
1 box corn muffin mix (use as thickener in place of starch/flavoring)
1/4 cup agave syrup
1/4 stick REAL butter
Oil either olive or sunflower

1 whole sweet yellow onion---
1 15.5Oz can mexican stewed tomatoes---blend in blender add to browned meat
1 15.5Oz can italian stewed tomatoes-

4 garlic pods(crush with flat of knife) add to browned meat, remove from finished chili

>>51365230
cooking

wash, strain and soak beans then set aside

mix all dry seasoning in a bowl

add a splash of oil to your pan/pot/dutch-oven heat on medium add butter to make clarified butter

add meat to HOT clarified butter, stir every few minutes otherwise keep it covered till it browns (it doesn't matter if it has a lot of fats or whatever your going to drain it)

peal outer layer of onion and chop off the ends, add to blender with tomatoes, don't drain the tomatoes.

drain your meat and put it back in the pan/pot/dutch-oven, add garlic, 1 tsp of season mix, 1 cup water and all tomato/onion puree, mix and let heat to simmer.

mix about 4 tbsp of corn muffin mix with 1.5 cups water or whatever flavor/thickness is good for you, use your judgment if you know what your doing,
otherwise follow the directions

drain and add beans to crock pot add seasoning mix, meat mix, and cornbread mix, stir well, cover and set to high for an hour, then low for two, stir every half hour.
